Business Brief -- SelecTronics Inc.:
   Fuji Xerox Co. of Japan
   To Market New Products
As part of the marketing agreement, Fuji Xerox lent $1.4
million to SelecTronics in October 1991 and March 1992. The
loan was in the form of debentures that can be converted into
4.3 million shares of SelecTronics common stock, equal to
about 9.4% of its common shares outstanding.
   Fuji Xerox makes and markets home and office copiers and
computerized products. SelecTronics develops personal
electronic versions of reference materials, including the
Physicians Desk Reference, spelling checkers, the Bible and
Random House Encyclopedia.